üî© RAILS USED & U-POSITION (APPLICABLE ACROSS MULTIPLE ASSETS)

U-Position

Represents the vertical mounting position of equipment within a bay/rack.

Example: U1, U2, Top, Bottom, Front, Rear


Rails Used

Indicates whether the equipment is mounted on standard bay rails.

Typical values: Yes, No, or Integrated


üìå Used for: Rectifiers, Plant Panels, BDFB Panels, Batteries
üìå If unknown ‚Üí leave blank


---

üîã DC PLANT (Billington / Wilmington)

Required / Optional (if available):

Field	What to Provide

Custom Field ‚Äì Load Amps	Current DC load drawn from the plant
Float Voltage	Nominal DC voltage (e.g., ‚Äì48V)
Anticipated Load (A)	Expected future load (can match Load Amps)
Engineered Capacity	Maximum designed DC capacity
Discharge VPC	Voltage per cell during discharge (1.75 or 1.85)
Target Run Time (Hours)	Backup duration (e.g., 3 or 5 hours)


üìå Not Mandatory:
PDSC Distribution, Plant Bay, Financials, Audit fields, Planning fields


---

üîå GENERATOR

Generator ‚Äì Plymouth Meeting

Only field (optional):

Custom Field ‚Äì Maximum Load
Maximum electrical load (kW) the generator is expected to support.


üìå All other generator fields ‚Üí Not required


